ld notes and conversations with Securitate officers. Verdery also talks with some of the informers who were close friends, learning the complex circumstances that led them to report on her, and considers how fieldwork and spying can be easily confused. Part memoir, part detective story, part anthropological analysis, My Life as a Spy offers a personal account of how government surveillance worked during the Cold War and how Verdery experienced living under it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCold WarvPersonal narratives. 0aSecret servicevSourcesxHistoryy20th centuryzRomania. 0aSecret servicezRomaniaxHistoryy20th centuryvSources. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aethnographic memoir.  asurveillance dossier.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106963320 cprintz978082237066640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822371908423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822371908/original  a978-3-11-069633-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles